:" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a polygon overlay’s appearance using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:fillColorForPolygonAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"them. You should close the polygon by specifying the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as the first and last vertices; otherwise, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"polygon’s fill may not cover the area you expect it to. To avoid filling the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"space within the shape, give the polygon a transparent fill or use an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A polygon may have one or more interior polygons, or holes, that you specify as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" objects with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method. For example, if a polygon represents a lake, it could exclude an island","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"within the lake using an interior polygon. Interior polygons may not themselves","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"have interior polygons. To represent a shape that includes a polygon within a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hole or, more generally, to group multiple polygons together in one shape, use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" object.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To make the polygon straddle the antimeridian, specify some longitudes less"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"than −180 degrees or greater than 180 degrees."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Related-examples","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Related examples"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"TODO: Add a polygon annotation, learn how to initialize an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"text":" object from an array of coordinates.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon"]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"class","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNPolygon","title":"MLNPolygon","roleHeading":"Class","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPolygon","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MLNPolygon","kind":"identifier"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},{"type":"text","text":" object r